&lt;h1 id="pid-tuning-in-klipper">PID Tuning in Klipper&lt;a class="td-heading-self-link" href="#pid-tuning-in-klipper" aria-label="Heading self-link">&lt;/a>&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>PID tuning is essential for maintaining consistent temperatures in your 3D printer&amp;rsquo;s hot end and heat bed, leading to better print quality. Here&amp;rsquo;s a breakdown of PID tuning in Klipper:&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="what-is-pid-tuning">What is PID Tuning?&lt;a class="td-heading-self-link" href="#what-is-pid-tuning" aria-label="Heading self-link">&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>PID stands for Proportional-Integral-Derivative. It&amp;rsquo;s a method that helps the printer controller adjust heating power based on the difference between the desired temperature (setpoint) and the actual temperature reading from the sensor. By fine-tuning these adjustments, the printer maintains a stable temperature with minimal fluctuations.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Testing a Bltouch, CRTouch, ora clone in Klipper</title><link>https://minimal3dp.com/klipper-calibration/bltouch-testing/</link><pubDate>Mon, 06 May 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://minimal3dp.com/klipper-calibration/bltouch-testing/</guid><description>&lt;p>Testing a BLTouch with Klipper involves several steps to ensure that the probe is functioning correctly. Here&amp;rsquo;s a simplified process:&lt;/p>
&lt;ol>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Initial Setup&lt;/strong>: Make sure the BLTouch is correctly mounted and the pin is about 2 mm above the nozzle when retracted (1).&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Self-Test&lt;/strong>: Power on the printer; the BLTouch should perform a self-test, moving the pin up and down. After this, the pin should retract, and the red LED should light up (1).&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>